Package com.intellij.execution

Class Executor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.execution.Executor
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CoverageExecutor, DefaultDebugExecutor, DefaultRunExecutor

    public abstract class Executor
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes a specific way of executing any possible run configuration. The three default executors provided by the IntelliJ Platform by default are Run, Debug and Run with Coverage. Each executor gets its own toolbar button, which starts the selected run configuration using this executor, and its own context menu item for starting a configuration using this executor.
    See Also:
    ExecutorRegistry
